[8] Philippines
Date: 25 Jun 2007
Source: News.Balita.ph [edited]

The Iloilo City Health Office (CHO) here has
confirmed the deaths of 5 children due to dengue.
The CHO here was able to monitor 35 cases from
the period January to June this year [2007] with
5 recorded deaths.
Of the deaths, 2 were recorded in January and one
each in February, April and June [2007]. A
6-month old baby girl from Arevalo is the
youngest casualty while a 10-year old boy from
Zone 2-San Juan is the eldest.
Other casualties are 2-year old boy from Molo
Boulevard, 9-year old girl from Bakhaw,
Mandurriao, and another 4-year old boy from
Veterans Village, City Proper.
Health officer Dr. Urminico Baronda declared the
situation alarming, adding that the cases are
higher this year when compared with the same
period last year [2006]. From January to June
2006, the CHO has recorded 26 cases with 3
deaths. A total of 139 cases was documented for
the entire year.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett
A map of Iloilo Province, showing the location of
the city and relevant population data, can be
accessed at:
<http://www.answers.com/topic/iloilo-city>
